  %section.public-events
    %h2 Commands:
    
    %dl.methods 
      %dt goToRGB
      %dd Sets the color of the BlinkM RGB LED to the specified combination of RGB color provided (red, green and blue values should be between 0 and 255).
      %dt fadeToRGB
      %dd Fades the color of the BlinkM RGB LED to the specified combination of RGB color provided (red, green and blue values should be between 0 and 255).
      %dt fadeToHSB
      %dd Fades the color of the BlinkM RGB LED to the specified combination of HSB provided.
      %dt fadeToRandomRGB
      %dd Fades the color of the BlinkM RGB LED to a random combination of RGB color (red, green and blue values should be between 0 and 255).
      %dt fadeToRandomHSB
      %dd Fades the color of the BlinkM RGB LED to a random combination of HSB .
      %dt playLightScript
      %dd Plays a light script for the BlinkM RGB LED.
      %dt stopScript
      %dd Stops an specific script for the BlinkM RGB LED.
      %dt setFadeSpeed
      %dd Sets a fade to an specific speed for the BlinkM RGB LED.
      %dt setTimeAdjust
      %dd Sets a time adjust for the BlinkM RGB LED.
      %dt getRGBColor
      %dd Returns an array containing the RGB values for the current color (all integer between 0 and 255).
      %dt setAddress
      %dd Sets an address to the driver.
      %dt getAddress
      %dd Returns an sring describing the I2C addresss being used.
      %dt getFirmware
      %dd Returns an sring describing the I2C firmware version being used.
      %dt off
      %dd Turns BlinkM off.

    %h2 Events

    %dl.methods 
      %dt start
      %dd Sent when the device has been started and is ready to use.  

  %section.how-to
    %h2 How to use
    %p Example using a BlinkM.
    %h3 JavaScript
    :markdown
          :::javascript
          var Cylon = require('cylon');

          Cylon.robot({
            connection: { name: 'arduino', adaptor: 'firmata', port: '/dev/ttyACM0' },
            device: {name: 'led', driver: 'led', pin: 13},

            work: function(my) {
              every((1).seconds(), function() {my.led.toggle()});
            }
          }).start();

    %h3 CoffeeScript
    :markdown
          :::javascript
